rComments: Professor Boyd is amazing! She is a veteran in the field,and very knowledgeable about everything 'immigration'. She is super understanding, and more than willing to help if approached. She's an old school prof. who genuinely wants to engage her students, and does so with great course readings and relevant lectures
She also makes me miss my mom. She is a great professor and absolutely cares about knowing and teaching every single student personally. She is nice and I really respect her and her work!

Being a male in this course is hard as I learned by 1st hand experience. Most of the material will seem biased, but true nonetheless. Her marking is hard, but if you take the time to go to class and seek help, the material is more clear and will be reflected on your final grade, as I also learned. Lots of long readings that you MUST read 2 do well.
Though a hard marker, any course by Prof. Boyd is worth it. She makes a point of ensuring that most students take something away from the course.
She makes me miss my mom.  She is THAT caring.
Prof. Boyd is very caring and genuinely cares about the student. Her material and lectures are very engaging.
